newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: High dollar dampens European feeds trade.
newsitem.headline: High dollar dampens European feeds trade.

text.p: A strong dollar restricted business on the European meals and feeds market to a few trades this afternoon, market sources said.

"Even a late dip in the dollar coupled to a stronger Chicago soymeal futures opening failed to spark more demand. Problems with swine fever in the Netherlands, which could lead to lower compound feed sales also kept many buyers sidelined," one broker said.

Dutch high protein soymeal traded at $310 a tonne fob Rotterdam. Feb Argentine sunmeal pellets traded at $129 a tonne cif Rotterdam and March and April/June both at $120 cif.--KAREL LUIMES +31 20 504 5832
